{"id": "unknown-2026-04-29-005", "date": "2026-04-29", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Wed"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "negative", "score": -0.5, "keywords": ["uncertainty"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "India’s textile opportunity runs into a harder reality", "content": "India’s textile competitiveness is shifting from tariff advantage to trust, as policy uncertainty and geopolitical risks reshape sourcing decisions.\nThe Chabahar waiver expiry highlights how financing, compliance, and logistics ambiguity can outweigh cost benefits.\nWhile India retains scale, rising costs and uneven exports limit its ability to convert opportunity into share gains.", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/india-s-textile-opportunity-runs-into-a-harder-reality-309988-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-04-29-006", "date": "2026-04-29", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Wed"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "negative", "score": -0.5, "keywords": ["weak", "uncertainty"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "Polymer swings with crude volatility; textiles fail to recover", "content": "Polymers in India swung sharply with crude volatility, as ceasefire hopes briefly pushed prices down before a rebound reversed sentiment. \nProducers cut PP, PE and PVC prices significantly, yet textile demand failed to revive. \nWeak downstream offtake and rising uncertainty have kept buyers cautious, with markets remaining volatile and directionless.", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/polymer-swings-with-crude-volatility-textiles-fail-to-recover-309987-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-04-29-007", "date": "2026-04-29", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Wed"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "positive", "score": 0.5, "keywords": ["improve"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "US-EU-Japan alignment shifts global textile trade flows", "content": "Global textile supply chains are shifting from cost-driven globalisation to alliance-led networks prioritising security, traceability, and compliance.\nUS, EU, and Japan coordination is accelerating diversification towards trusted partners like India and Vietnam.\nWhile costs may rise due to stricter standards, improved resilience and market access are becoming central to long-term competitiveness.", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/us-eu-japan-alignment-shifts-global-textile-trade-flows-309985-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-04-29-008", "date": "2026-04-29", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Wed"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["cotton_price", "earnings"], "sentiment": {"label": "negative", "score": -0.5, "keywords": ["concerns", "weak"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.75, "reasons": ["涉及財報"]}, "title": "ICE cotton edges up on higher crude oil, dry weather concerns", "content": "ICE cotton futures edged higher, supported by firm crude oil prices and dry weather in the US, though gains were capped by easing geopolitical tensions.\nPlanting progress remained steady, while a weaker dollar and firm commodities supported demand.\nPrices stayed range-bound amid expected rains and mild profit-taking, with mixed early trade today.", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/ice-cotton-edges-up-on-higher-crude-oil-dry-weather-concerns-309984-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-04-29-009", "date": "2026-04-29", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Wed"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["fast_fashion", "supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "positive", "score": 0.5, "keywords": ["increase", "strong demand"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "US-Iran war pushes India denim prices up by $0.66/metre", "content": "India’s denim segment is seeing strong demand driven by fast fashion and affordable retail, but rising input costs amid geopolitical tensions are pushing fabric prices higher. \nIndustry players warn retail prices may increase as raw material and energy costs surge, even as demand remains steady with orders booked for the next few months ahead.", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/us-iran-war-pushes-india-denim-prices-up-by-0-66-metre-309983-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-04-29-010", "date": "2026-04-29", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Wed"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "positive", "score": 0.5, "keywords": ["improve"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "World Bank approves $300 mn for Cambodia logistics upgrade", "content": "As gaps in resilient transport links and logistics capacity constrain Cambodia’s trade and regional connectivity, the World Bank has approved the first phase of the Multiphase Programmatic Approach Cambodia Regional Connectivity Improvement programme. \nIt will improve resilient transport connectivity along sections of the Asian Highway 21 corridor and strengthen national logistics management capacity. ", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/world-bank-approves-300-mn-for-cambodia-logistics-upgrade-309979-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
