{"id": "unknown-2026-04-29-012", "date": "2026-04-29", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Wed"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["earnings"], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.17, "keywords": ["growth", "increase", "slow"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.75, "reasons": ["涉及財報"]}, "title": "Euro area consumers expect higher inflation, slower growth ahead: ECB", "content": "Euro area consumers grew more pessimistic in March 2026 as inflation expectations rose, with one-year ahead forecasts reaching 4 per cent, as per ECB. \nSpending expectations strengthened, while income outlook remained unchanged. \nGrowth expectations fell to -2.1 per cent and unemployment expectations increased. \nConsumers also expected higher house prices and mortgage rates, signalling a cautious outlook. ", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/euro-area-consumers-expect-higher-inflation-slower-growth-ahead-ecb-309967-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "adidas-2026-04-29-013", "date": "2026-04-29", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Wed"}, "entities": {"companies": ["adidas"], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["fast_fashion", "earnings"], "sentiment": {"label": "positive", "score": 0.5, "keywords": ["growth", "increase"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.75, "reasons": ["涉及財報"]}, "title": "Germany’s Adidas posts strong Q1 on DTC momentum, broad demand", "content": "Adidas has reported a strong Q1 2026, with revenue rising 14 per cent YoY to €6.6 billion (~$7.72 billion), driven by robust DTC growth and broad-based demand. \nOperating profit increased 16 per cent to €705 million (~$824.85 million). \nApparel and performance segments led gains. \nThe company expects high single-digit sales growth and ~€2.3 billion (~$2.69 billion) operating profit in 2026. ", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_apparel", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/apparel-news/germany-s-adidas-posts-strong-q1-on-dtc-momentum-broad-demand-309986-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-04-29-014", "date": "2026-04-29", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Wed"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": []}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "Chinese team visits Bangladesh, discusses FDI in textile sector", "content": "A Chinese delegation met BGMEA to explore foreign direct investment (FDI) and technology partnerships in Bangladesh’s textile sector, focusing on MMF, synthetic fibres and technical textiles. \nBangladesh highlighted its $8–9 billion fabric import market as a key opportunity. \nTalks also covered sustainability, training and B2B linkages to boost sector modernisation. ", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_apparel", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/apparel-news/chinese-team-visits-bangladesh-discusses-fdi-in-textile-sector-309968-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-04-29-015", "date": "2026-04-29", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Wed"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "positive", "score": 0.5, "keywords": ["growth"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "FTA to boost competitiveness of Indian garments in New Zealand", "content": "The India–New Zealand FTA grants 100 per cent duty-free access to textiles and apparel, improving price competitiveness and margins by 5-10 per cent.\nDuty-free wool imports strengthen raw material security, supporting value-added segments.\nWhile the $1.9 billion market is small, it offers stable demand and scope for premium positioning and long-term export growth.", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_apparel", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/apparel-news/fta-to-boost-competitiveness-of-indian-garments-in-new-zealand-309960-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-04-29-016", "date": "2026-04-29", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Wed"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "positive", "score": 0.5, "keywords": ["growth", "expand"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "India-New Zealand FTA to open new avenues for growth: T&A industry", "content": "India’s textile industry has welcomed the India-New Zealand Free Trade Agreement (FTA), citing 100 per cent duty-free access as a boost to competitiveness and market diversification.\nIndustry leaders said the pact will expand exports, support value-added segments, and strengthen resilience amid global disruptions, while creating jobs and enhancing long-term trade growth.", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_apparel", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/apparel-news/india-new-zealand-fta-to-open-new-avenues-for-growth-t-a-industry-309975-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
